---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lang = 'en' as const;
---
<BaseLayout
  lang={lang}
  title="About — AStyltsvig Consulting"
  description="Andreas Sørbye Styltsvig runs AStyltsvig Consulting as a single-person practice in Copenhagen — full-stack development in Vue and Laravel, and AI productivity consulting."
>
  <article class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-24 md:pt-32 pb-16">
    <p class="fade-in font-[var(--font-mono)] text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[var(--color-muted)]">About</p>
    <h1 class="fade-in !mt-4 max-w-[16ch]">
      One developer. <span class="grad-text">Deep focus.</span>
    </h1>

    <div class="fade-in mt-16 glass p-8 md:p-12 prose-body">
      <p class="!mt-0 text-lg">
        I'm Andreas Sørbye Styltsvig, and I run <strong>AStyltsvig Consulting</strong> as a single-person practice out of Vanløse, Copenhagen.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've been working in web development for more than a decade, and my focus over the last few years has been full-stack development in <strong>Vue and Laravel</strong> — particularly for organisations where the system needs to live for many years and hold up under actual use, not just a demo.
      </p>
      <p>
        Since late 2025 a growing part of my practice is <strong>AI productivity consulting</strong>: helping development teams move from ad-hoc chatbot use to a real AI-assisted workflow. I don't sell it as theory — I use it every day on my own production systems, and I can show the difference it makes.
      </p>

      <h2>What I can help with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Establishing an AI-assisted workflow (Claude Code, Cursor) that holds up under production code review</li>
        <li>Building and maintaining web applications in Vue/Laravel</li>
        <li>Migrating older sites (typically WordPress) to modern, static stacks</li>
        <li>Taking over ownership of DNS, email, and domain administration from a previous vendor</li>
        <li>Advising on technical architecture, vendor selection, and operational setup</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I don't do</h2>
      <p>
        Pure frontend design without development, SEO-as-a-service, paid advertising, or "quick fixes" on systems I don't have the chance to understand properly. I'd rather take on fewer clients and go deep with each of them.
      </p>

      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        I've worked closely with several Danish organisations, including <strong>Danske Døves Landsforbund</strong> and <strong>Døveforeningen af 1866</strong>. My flagship product is the ERP system I've built and operated for <a href="https://mallard.dk" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Mallard</strong></a>, a Danish sign-language interpreting provider, since 2022 — and the proving ground where I've refined how AI-assisted development actually works in sustained production.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
